<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8437&amp;p=87859#p87859"><![CDATA[
I recall there were some major problem with Super Spy Hunter (I think) when 8 sprites limit is disabled in an emulator. Something that affected to the gameplay - not allowed to shot when too many objects are on screen or something like that.<br /><br />I once made an 'overclocked' build of NNNesterJ by someone's request. As I recall, I simply changed t-states table to make all the opcodes 1 cycle long, instead of actually overclocking the CPU with all the pitch etc related things. That removed slowdowns in Contra Force, but of course introduces bugs in some games.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Thu Dec 22, 2011 6:44 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
