I think tepples suggested copying the Dendy's idea of adding more dead scanlines before VBlank as a way of helping with slowdown without resorting to overclocking. But to prevent pitch and audio problems you'd want to disable APU updates during this free cpu catch up time.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Thu Dec 22, 2011 6:36 pm</p><hr />
